'''Mini Project: Portfolio Risk–Return Analyzer

This mini project uses:
✔ Arrays
✔ Daily returns
✔ Mean return
✔ Variance
✔ Volatility (std dev)
✔ Covariance
✔ Correlation
✔ Dot product



Problem Statement

A client invests in three mutual funds:

Fund	Units	NAV Day-1	NAV Day-2	NAV Day-3	NAV Day-4	NAV Day-5
Equity	250	150	        153	        149	        155	        160
Debt	400	104	        105	        106	        107	        108
Liquid	1000	10.45	        10.46	        10.47	        10.48	        10.49

Your tasks:

Create a returns matrix for the 3 funds.

Compute average return of each fund.

Compute volatility of each fund.

Compute correlation matrix between funds.

Compute portfolio daily returns using weights.

Compute portfolio volatility.
'''

print('Mini Project: Portfolio Risk–Return Analyzer')



import numpy as np

# 1️NAV data for 5 days (rows = days, columns = funds)
nav_data = np.array([
    [150, 104, 10.45],
    [153, 105, 10.46],
    [149, 106, 10.47],
    [155, 107, 10.48],
    [160, 108, 10.49]
])

# 2  Portfolio units
units = np.array([250, 400, 1000])

# 3️ Calculate daily returns
returns = (nav_data[1:] - nav_data[:-1]) / nav_data[:-1]
print("Daily Returns Matrix:\n", returns)

# 4️ Mean return per fund
mean_returns = np.mean(returns, axis=0)
print("\nMean Returns:", mean_returns)

# 5️Volatility (std deviation)
volatility = np.std(returns, axis=0)
print("Volatility per Fund:", volatility)

# 6️ Correlation matrix
correlation = np.corrcoef(returns.T)
print("\nCorrelation Matrix:\n", correlation)

# 7️ Calculate fund values
values = nav_data[-1] * units
total_value = np.sum(values)
weights = values / total_value
print("\nPortfolio Weights:", weights)

# 8️ Portfolio daily returns using dot product
portfolio_daily_returns = returns.dot(weights)
print("\nPortfolio Daily Returns:", portfolio_daily_returns)

# 9️Portfolio Volatility
portfolio_volatility = np.std(portfolio_daily_returns)
print("\nPortfolio Volatility:", portfolio_volatility)
